==Demographics==
===Population and Homeownership===
As of 2021,<ref>{{cite web |title=Cherry Valley, AR |url=https://datausa.io/profile/geo/cherry-valley-ar#demographics |website=datausa.io |publisher=Data USA |access-date=November 9, 2023}}</ref> Cherry Valley had a population of 618 people, a 12% decrease since 2020, and 218 households. The median household income was $42,500 and the median property value was $65,300. The homeownership rate was 68.3%, while 77.2% of homeowners have a mortgage. 11.8% of the population lived under the [[poverty | poverty line]], most of whom being white females between the ages of 55 and 64.

