===Transportation===

The average household owned 2 cars, while 74.6% of inhabitants drove alone. 23.1% of the population carpooled, and the rest (1.52%) walked. The average commute time was 29 minutes.

===Healthcare===

19.9%<ref>{{cite web |title=US Census Data |url=https://datausa.io/profile/geo/cherry-valley-ar#health |website=datausa.io |publisher=Data USA |access-date=November 9, 2023}}</ref> of people were uninsured. 35.1% of people were under [[Medicaid]], 26.1% were under employer coverage, 11% were under [[Medicare (United States)|Medicare]], 7.12% were under an individual policy, and 0.809% were using [[United States Department of Veterans Affairs|VA]] healthcare.

